    • Constructor Detail

      • QGisLayer

        public QGisLayer(String name,
                 String path)
        Creates a new instance of a qgis layer. For each geometry layer, a QGisRenderer must be created (for use cases look at package layerTemplates).

        If the layer input is a csv file, you also need to specify a delimiter (e.g. , or ;) and the header names of the columns that contain the x and y coordinates (by setXField and setYField).
        Parameters:
        name - a unique name for the layer (as it is displayed in qgis later)
        path - the path to the input file
        geometryType - the type of geometry (none, point, line, polygon)
